# Osteóplus v2.9 — Cursor Rules

You are working on `osteoplus-v2.9`, the Osteóplus responsive PWA landing-page project — a Barcelona osteopathy, physiotherapy, and rehabilitation product. Always follow these rules when generating or modifying code in this repository.

---

## Source of truth

Before making any setup or implementation decision, consult the project source files in this priority order:

1. `docs/project-source/osteoplus-design-system.md` — tokens, accessibility, typography, layout, motion, component behavior.
2. `docs/project-source/brand-kit.md` — brand identity, logo rules, voice, spelling, v4.2 token migration.
3. `docs/project-source/style-guide.md` — writing, bilingual, casing, copy restrictions.
4. `docs/project-source/osteoplus-project-dna.md` — product scope, stack, architecture, definition of done.
5. `docs/project-source/ui-kit.md` — component maturity, variants, props, accessibility requirements.
6. `docs/preview/*.html` and `docs/preview/colors_and_type.css` — visual examples and token checks.

Legacy paths under `documents/` and `preview/` are also valid if `docs/project-source/` copies have not been created yet.

If documents conflict, use the newest approved source. For visual tokens, apply the **v4.2 migration**:

- Filled CTA: Teal-700 `#0F766E`
- Brand border / icon emphasis / logo fill: Teal-600 `#0D9488`
- Accent default: Orange-700 `#C2410C`
- Focus ring: Teal-500 `#14B8A6`

---

## Required stack

Do not deviate from this stack unless the user explicitly approves:

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 App Router (do not upgrade to 16 without approval)
- **React**: React 19
- **Language**: TypeScript strict (`noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, `noImplicitOverride`)
- **Package manager**: pnpm
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with semantic CSS variables in `src/app/globals.css`
- **UI primitives**: Source-owned shadcn/Radix-style components
- **Animation**: Framer Motion (must respect `prefers-reduced-motion`)
- **Forms**: react-hook-form + zod + `@hookform/resolvers`
- **i18n**: next-intl (Spanish default, English secondary)
- **Theme**: next-themes with `class` strategy
- **PWA**: `@ducanh2912/next-pwa`
- **Icons**: lucide-react only (2 px stroke, round cap/join)
- **Dates**: date-fns with `es` and `en-GB` locale support
- **Lint/format**: Biome
- **Testing**: Vitest, Playwright, axe-core, Lighthouse CI

---

## Non-negotiables

These rules apply to every file you generate or modify. Never violate them:

- Spanish (`es`) is the default locale. English (`en`) must have parity.
- Every user-facing string must come from `next-intl` messages. Never hard-code UI copy in components.
- Every screen and component must support dark and light mode.
- Use semantic design tokens only in components. Raw hex values are allowed only in `:root`, `.dark`, manifest metadata, static asset metadata, or one-time migration scripts.
- WCAG 2.2 AA is required.
- Touch targets: ≥ 48 × 48 px. Primary CTAs: ≥ 56 × 48 px.
- Body text ≥ 16 px (18 px preferred for senior-facing). Input text ≥ 16 px.
- Visible focus rings are required.
- All interactive elements need visible labels or accessible names.
- No placeholder-only form labels.
- No pre-checked consent boxes.
- No color-only indicators.
- Motion must respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- No parallax, autoplay media, or decorative animation.
- No emoji in UI chrome, copy, or gamification.
- Use Lucide icons with 2 px stroke and round cap/join.
- Spell the brand exactly as **Osteóplus** with the accented `ó`. Never write `Osteoplus`, `OsteoPlus`, `Osteo+`, or `osteo plus`.

---

## Brand and copy rules

Write like a trusted family osteopath explaining something in plain language.

**Always:**

- Write Spanish first, then English.
- Use warm, clinical-clear, quietly confident language.
- Use sentence case for all UI text (buttons, headings, nav, labels, modals, toasts, empty states).
- Use plain symptom-based language.
- Include a clear way forward in errors and safety copy.
- Include a clinic phone escape hatch in safety-critical flows.

**Never:**

- Use hype words (`revolutionary`, `seamless`, `cutting-edge`).
- Use minimizing words (`simply`, `just`, `easily`) when they could blame the user.
- Use jargon when plain language works.
- Use exclamation marks in UI chrome.
- Use ALL CAPS for emphasis.
- Use emoji.

---

## Project structure

```text
src/
  app/
    [locale]/
      layout.tsx
      page.tsx
    api/
    globals.css
    manifest.ts
    robots.ts
    sitemap.ts
  components/
    brand/          # Logo, brand-mark components
    landing/        # Landing-page sections (hero, services, footer, etc.)
    ui/             # Reusable primitives (button, theme-toggle, etc.)
    domain/         # Product-specific reusable components (beyond landing)
    patterns/       # Shared layout/interaction patterns
    providers.tsx   # ThemeProvider + context wrappers
  i18n/
    routing.ts
    request.ts
  lib/
    schemas/        # Zod form schemas
    theme/          # Theme utilities
    utils/          # General utilities (cn, clsx helpers)
  messages/
    es.json
    en.json
public/
  fonts/
  icons/
  logos/
docs/
  project-source/
  preview/
  qa/
```

- `/components/ui` → reusable primitives.
- `/components/landing` → landing-page sections.
- `/components/domain` → product-specific components reused beyond the landing page.

---

## Commands

```bash
pnpm install        # Install dependencies
pnpm dev            # Start dev server
pnpm build          # Production build
pnpm check          # Biome check
pnpm check:write    # Biome format + safe lint fixes
pnpm typecheck      # tsc --noEmit
pnpm test           # Vitest
pnpm e2e            # Playwright
pnpm validate       # check + typecheck + test + build
```

Before finalizing any significant change, run at minimum:

```bash
pnpm check && pnpm typecheck && pnpm build
```

Run Playwright and axe when UI behavior, accessibility, routing, theme, or i18n changes.

---

## Styling rules

- Define all colors as semantic CSS variables in `src/app/globals.css`.
- Consume tokens through Tailwind utilities and CSS variables.
- Never introduce one-off colors.
- Never use opacity hacks for disabled, hover, or active states.
- Use border-first, shadow-light design.
- Use the 4-point spacing grid.
- Radius tokens: button/input `8px`, card `12px`, modal `16px`, hero containers `24px`, chips `9999px`. No `radius/xs` token.
- Focus state: 2 px ring, 2 px offset.

### Key semantic tokens (v4.2)

| Token | Light | Dark |
|---|---|---|
| `--color-brand-primary` (CTA fill) | `#0F766E` Teal-700 | `#2DD4BF` |
| `--color-border-brand` (logo/border) | `#0D9488` Teal-600 | `#2DD4BF` |
| `--color-border-focus` | `#14B8A6` Teal-500 | `#5EEAD4` |
| `--color-accent-default` | `#C2410C` Orange-700 | `#FB923C` |

---

## Component rules

When creating or modifying any component:

- Add TypeScript props. Never use `any`.
- Use semantic tokens only — no raw hex in component files.
- Support dark mode.
- Support keyboard navigation when interactive.
- Include loading, error, disabled, focus, hover, and pressed states when relevant.
- Add `aria-label` for icon-only buttons.
- Use visible labels for form controls.
- Touch targets ≥ 48 × 48 px. Primary CTAs ≥ 56 × 48 px.
- Framer Motion only for purposeful transitions. Always respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

---

## i18n rules

- Route through `/[locale]`.
- Default locale: `es`. Supported: `es`, `en`.
- Redirect `/` → `/es`.
- Message files: `src/messages/es.json` and `src/messages/en.json`.
- Keep message keys stable across updates.
- Never merge a feature if one locale is missing required strings.
- Spanish copy is the source; English follows with tone parity.

---

## Forms and privacy

- Use react-hook-form + zod.
- Put schemas in `src/lib/schemas/`.
- Validate on blur and on submit.
- Focus the first invalid field on submit.
- Consent checkboxes default unchecked.
- Never transmit pain scores, mood data, or health-sensitive details to analytics.
- Do not implement medical diagnosis, AI triage, prescriptions, or emergency workflows unless explicitly scoped.

---

## PWA

- Provide manifest metadata (raw hex is acceptable in manifest).
- Add approved icons when assets are available.
- Provide offline fallback or clear offline state before production handoff.
- Never cache sensitive health data in unsafe storage.

---

## Logo and assets

- Use SVG logo variants from `public/logos/`.
- Primary Teal on light neutral surfaces.
- Teal-300 on dark surfaces.
- White on brand-colored or dark photo surfaces.
- Original for full-color marketing.
- Never stretch, skew, recolor, shadow, or rasterize the logo below target size.
- Preserve the accented `Ó`.

Expected logo files:

```text
public/logos/osteoplus-original-logo.svg
public/logos/osteoplus-logo-white.svg
public/logos/osteoplus-logo-teal-300.svg
public/logos/osteoplus-logo-primary-teal.svg
public/logos/osteoplus-logo-black.svg
public/logos/favicon.svg
```

---

## Git conventions

Use conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `test:`.

Before opening or summarizing a PR, include:

- What changed.
- How it was tested.
- Any skipped checks and why.
- Accessibility, i18n, and dark-mode considerations.
- Remaining TODOs.

---

## Initialization phases

The project follows a phased plan (full details in `osteoplus-v2.9-detailed-plan.md`):

0. **Preflight** — verify Node ≥ 20.9, pnpm, Git.
1. **Protect existing folder** — backup, scaffold if needed, pin Next.js 15 + React 19.
2. **Normalize source documents** — copy into `docs/` and `public/`.
3. **Agent guidance** — place `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.cursorrules` at repo root.
4. **Agent tooling** — configure Context7, UI UX Pro Max, 21st.dev Magic.
5. **Dependencies** — install runtime and dev packages.
6. **Scripts** — configure pnpm scripts.
7. **Biome + TypeScript** — configure linting and strict TypeScript.
8. **App structure** — create the `src/` directory tree.
9. **Tailwind + tokens** — set up `globals.css` with v4.2 semantic tokens.
10. **i18n** — routing, request config, starter messages in `es` and `en`.
11. **Theme provider** — next-themes with class strategy.
12. **PWA manifest** — metadata with approved icons.
13. **Landing components** — hero, services, booking strip, trust, footer.
14. **Testing + QA** — axe, Playwright, viewport checks, hex audit.
15. **Validation** — `pnpm check && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm build`.

### Assumptions and missing inputs

- Merriweather variable font may be missing — create `public/fonts/` and add a TODO.
- Production clinic phone, booking backend URL, and analytics policy are not provided — use placeholders.
- Supabase schema and API contracts are not provided — do not implement backend booking logic.
- Do not implement full booking flow until backend/API scope is supplied.

